arth went around the sun, and another three or four hundred years to forgive the man that pointed it out to them. And even today some of them expect me to believe they know the directions to heaven. Right, and witches float. &#10;As far as I'm concerned, our society will progress if students who leave to go to a church or mosque during school hours, and don't return to classes, keep on walking until they are in a country that isn't Canada. If they stay and are encouraged to become indoctrinated we'll just waste energy shouting at one another and whining about discrimination like the article mentions. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="911" language="en" documentId="1542" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="LittleBrother" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1542" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="532"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="533" end="911"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>